Troubleshooting

The HTML report generated by IBM Rational Rhapsody ReporterPLUS is using a JAVA applet as a tree browser. This applet supports a functionality called "Locate" which allows navigation from the right hand side pane to the left hand side tree.

This applet requires the JAVA 2 Runtime Environment to be installed on your machine. A mismatch between the JRE version and the applet may result in a gray area that looks like this:




To solve the problem you may follow one of these two procedures:


Install  JAVA 2 Runtime and reopen this report.


I want to use an older applet and not use the "Locate" button


If from any reason you cannot download and install the JRE, you may use an older version of this applet that does not require this specific JRE. Note that this older applet does not support the "Locate" functionality. This feature helps you find a specific model element in the browser.

To use the older version of the applet first close all the browser windows. You can disable the "Locate" functiobality in ReporterPLUS  by unchecking "Support Locate in Browser" option. This can be done from "View->Default Document Properties" in HTML page. If this "Locate" functionality needs to be disabled specific to template then it can be set from "File->Template Properties" dialog.
Once done, close the browser and reopen the generated document.
